      "writtenOn": "2017-05-16T18:53:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Putting it all together, I’m thinking of something like:\n\n  const char* kURLParameterKeys[] \u003d {\"prod\", \"ver\", \"guid\"};\n  for (auto key : kURLParameterKeys) {\n    const auto it \u003d parameters.find(key);\n    if (it !\u003d parameters.end()) {\n      url_.append(\n          base::StringPrintf(\"%c%s\u003d%s\",\n                             url_.find(\u0027?\u0027) \u003d\u003d std::string::npos ? \u0027?\u0027 : \u0027\u0026\u0027,\n                             key,\n                             it-\u003ec_str()));\n    }\n  }\n\nNoting that this will put \"prod\" and \"ver\" in the URL instead of \"product\" and \"version\". If you’re not equipped to deal with that on the server, then replace kURLParameterKeys[] with a struct{const char*; const char*;} to map from one set of names to the other.",
      "revId": "7ec80327f39523555b1d599e4246db6717f0a678",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
